WEBVTT

00:13.113 --> 00:16.115
[dramatic music]

00:16.117 --> 00:24.023
♪

00:42.308 --> 00:44.777
- Mind if I split?

00:44.779 --> 00:46.211
- Sure.

01:24.350 --> 01:26.351
All yours.

01:34.094 --> 01:35.661
- Hi.

01:35.663 --> 01:36.662
- Hi.

01:36.664 --> 01:38.564
- Oh, god.

01:38.566 --> 01:40.432
I'm sorry.

01:40.434 --> 01:41.567
- That's okay.

01:41.569 --> 01:44.369
- It was nice to meet you.

01:51.111 --> 01:52.845
[alarm clock buzzing]

02:03.123 --> 02:04.423
[buzzing stops]

02:11.264 --> 02:12.898
- Hello, friend.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.134
- Hello, friend.

02:17.270 --> 02:20.606
- Have you been swimming
already?

02:20.608 --> 02:21.740
- Mm-hmm.

02:21.742 --> 02:24.209
- Oh, jesus.

02:33.553 --> 02:36.155
I don't think
we have time.

02:39.792 --> 02:41.827
[giggles]

03:09.389 --> 03:10.722
- Mom!

03:10.724 --> 03:12.558
- Oh.

03:12.560 --> 03:13.959
- Are you awake?

03:13.961 --> 03:15.961
- Oh.
- Mom.

03:15.963 --> 03:18.330
- [groans]

03:18.332 --> 03:20.465
When is she going to college?
- 12 years.

03:20.467 --> 03:22.501
- Mom!

03:24.270 --> 03:26.238
- Oh.
- [groans]

03:41.888 --> 03:43.488
- Where's my shoe?

03:43.490 --> 03:45.257
- Have fun loading the van.

03:53.366 --> 03:54.700
- Nice ass.

04:11.751 --> 04:12.851
- You packed?

04:12.853 --> 04:15.287
- Yep.
- You excited?

04:16.889 --> 04:19.324
You're hiding it well,
but I can tell that you are.

04:19.326 --> 04:20.792
- I want to stay here
for the summer.

04:20.794 --> 04:22.661
- I know.

04:22.663 --> 04:24.029
- I want to go to league camp.

04:24.031 --> 04:26.598
- Well, next summer,
if you get that gpa up,

04:26.600 --> 04:28.367
You can stay
and go to league camp.

04:28.369 --> 04:29.735
- That's ridiculous.

04:29.737 --> 04:31.536
- Why is that ridiculous?

04:31.538 --> 04:33.338
- You said
I can go to league camp.

04:33.340 --> 04:35.407
- If you get
your grades up.

04:35.409 --> 04:37.643
You seem to have forgotten the
second clause of the contract.

04:37.645 --> 04:39.011
- It sucks at grandpa's.

04:39.013 --> 04:41.813
- That's not true.
- It is true.

04:41.815 --> 04:43.915
- Martin, your grandfather
has a swimming pool,

04:43.917 --> 04:46.285
Two tennis courts, and a sauna
on his property.

04:46.287 --> 04:49.021
It categorically
does not suck.

04:49.023 --> 04:51.423
- You suck.

04:51.425 --> 04:53.759
- That's a more defendable
hypothesis.

04:53.761 --> 04:57.362
- Oh, shit.
I've been looking for that.

04:57.364 --> 04:58.363
- No, wait!

05:01.901 --> 05:03.635
- That was not my fault.

05:03.637 --> 05:06.838
- I believe that it was.

05:06.840 --> 05:10.642
[footsteps approaching]

05:10.644 --> 05:13.845
Trevor,
come here a second.

05:15.381 --> 05:18.050
What are you gonna read
this summer?

05:18.052 --> 05:19.785
Come on, man,

05:19.787 --> 05:21.787
You got three glorious,
uninhibited months ahead of you,

05:21.789 --> 05:23.822
And you got a whole bookshelf
in front of you.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.557
Pretty soon
you're gonna be 9,

05:25.559 --> 05:27.326
Then you'll be 10,
then you'll get a job,

05:27.328 --> 05:28.927
Then you meet a girl,
and then you'll have kids.

05:28.929 --> 05:30.996
You will never have the chance
to read for pleasure

05:30.998 --> 05:32.397
Ever again.

05:32.399 --> 05:34.966
Seize this opportunity,
little man.

05:34.968 --> 05:36.702
- Oh, not that one.

05:36.704 --> 05:38.804
- Why not?
- 'cause you're too young.

05:38.806 --> 05:40.072
- But I want to read dad's book.

05:40.074 --> 05:41.673
- Well, when you're older.

05:41.675 --> 05:44.810
- Why? Is it dirty?

05:44.812 --> 05:47.346
- No. It's derivative.

05:47.348 --> 05:49.681
- Told you not to read
the reviews.

05:49.683 --> 05:51.383
- You were right.

05:53.453 --> 05:55.954
- Mr. Solloway, hi.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.556
Thanks for coming in.

05:57.558 --> 06:00.826
- Not like I had
much of a choice.

06:00.828 --> 06:03.562
- Well, we'll try not to take up
too much of your time.

06:03.564 --> 06:06.098
I'd like to begin by asking you
a few questions

06:06.100 --> 06:08.433
About how this whole mess
got started.

06:08.435 --> 06:09.501
- Morning, daughter.

06:09.503 --> 06:11.737
- Good morning, father.

06:11.739 --> 06:14.139
- Is that all right
with you?

06:14.141 --> 06:18.110
- It's a free country, pal.
Ask away.

06:18.112 --> 06:19.911
You need your sunglasses
in the car?

06:19.913 --> 06:22.481
- I'm breaking them in.

06:22.483 --> 06:25.117
- All right, you think we got
everything?

06:25.119 --> 06:26.885
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah?

06:26.887 --> 06:28.987
Okay.

06:28.989 --> 06:31.089
Here we go. Hop in.

06:32.859 --> 06:34.593
Where's martin?

06:34.595 --> 06:36.061
- He's still in the house,
isn't he?

06:36.063 --> 06:37.629
- I don't think so.

06:37.631 --> 06:40.132
[keys clatter]
shoot. Here.

06:46.072 --> 06:48.006
- Martin!

06:50.476 --> 06:52.144
Martin!

06:52.146 --> 06:56.548
- So can you tell us a bit
about who you were back then...

06:56.550 --> 06:58.417
Mr. Solloway?

06:58.419 --> 07:00.619
- I don't understand
the question.

07:00.621 --> 07:02.621
What exactly
do you want to know?

07:02.623 --> 07:04.656
Martin!

07:09.162 --> 07:11.696
- Anything you think
is relevant.

07:13.900 --> 07:16.435
How were you feeling
about your life?

07:18.204 --> 07:21.640
- Fine. Fine.

07:21.642 --> 07:23.642
Martin! Come on, dude!
This isn't funny.

07:23.644 --> 07:25.844
Everyone's waitin' on you.

07:28.514 --> 07:30.649
- Can you say a little more?

07:30.651 --> 07:33.585
- Great.
I was feeling great, you know?

07:33.587 --> 07:35.987
My children were healthy.
My wife was beautiful.

07:38.724 --> 07:41.026
My life was
pretty fucking perfect.

07:43.863 --> 07:45.130
Jesus!

07:45.132 --> 07:48.667
Jesus!

07:48.669 --> 07:50.702
[grunting]

07:50.704 --> 07:52.604
Christ.

07:58.211 --> 08:00.178
[breathing heavily]
it's okay.

08:00.180 --> 08:03.615
You're fine.

08:03.617 --> 08:06.685
Martin, it's okay.

08:06.687 --> 08:08.587
- [giggling]

08:08.589 --> 08:09.621
- Oh, jesus.

08:09.623 --> 08:11.823
What the fuck?

08:11.825 --> 08:12.958
Jesus.

08:12.960 --> 08:14.759
[shouting] get up!
- Ow, dad!

08:14.761 --> 08:16.161
What the fuck?!
- Come on, get out.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.563
Get in there.
Get in there.

08:18.565 --> 08:20.966
What is wrong with you?!
- It was a joke.

08:20.968 --> 08:22.501
- Oh, you think that's funny.
You think killing yourself is--

08:22.503 --> 08:23.969
- I didn't kill myself.

08:23.971 --> 08:25.737
I faked a hanging.
It's totally different.

08:25.739 --> 08:27.138
It was really hard
to figure out.

08:27.140 --> 08:28.240
I had to look it up online.

08:28.242 --> 08:29.875
- Are you insane?

08:29.877 --> 08:31.610
Take that off. Take it off.
- Ow.

08:31.612 --> 08:34.513
- Take it off.

08:34.515 --> 08:36.648
Everyone's in the car
waiting for you.

08:36.650 --> 08:38.517
Is it so much to ask
that for one day,

08:38.519 --> 08:39.985
One day in your entire life,

08:39.987 --> 08:42.787
You think of somebody
other than yourself?

08:42.789 --> 08:45.524
- I thought
you'd be proud of me.

08:54.534 --> 08:57.636
- Dude.

08:57.638 --> 09:00.805
What is goin' on with you?

09:00.807 --> 09:02.741
Last summer
you were this happy guy.

09:02.743 --> 09:04.809
What happened?

09:11.884 --> 09:13.618
Come on.

09:13.620 --> 09:17.188
Let's go
before your mother comes up.

09:17.190 --> 09:19.057
- I hate grandpa.

09:19.059 --> 09:21.326
- I know, so do I.

09:21.328 --> 09:23.962
Look at it this way.
At least you stand to inherit

09:23.964 --> 09:25.897
Some of his money when he dies.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.799
- I won't take a penny of it.

09:27.801 --> 09:30.168
- Martin,
I'm a public school teacher.

09:30.170 --> 09:32.103
- So?
- Take the money.

09:37.910 --> 09:39.077
- Is everything okay?
- Ow!

09:39.079 --> 09:42.047
- Hey, careful.
Everything okay?

09:42.049 --> 09:43.582
- It's fine.

09:47.653 --> 09:49.688
- What happened?

09:49.690 --> 09:51.923
- He couldn't find
his bathing suit.

09:51.925 --> 09:53.725
- Oh, I packed it for you,
honey.

09:53.727 --> 09:56.061
- One, two, three, four.
That's all of 'em, right?

09:56.063 --> 09:58.597
- Yep, that I know of.

10:05.271 --> 10:08.273
[somber music]

10:08.275 --> 10:16.281
♪

11:02.928 --> 11:05.196
- Whit, can you please
take those off inside?

11:05.198 --> 11:08.199
- I'm sure I can.

11:08.201 --> 11:10.301
Hey!
- Where were you last night?

11:10.303 --> 11:11.870
- I was at courtney's.

11:11.872 --> 11:13.171
- What were you doing
at courtney's?

11:13.173 --> 11:14.873
- Hey, what can I
get you all?

11:14.875 --> 11:16.141
- We were studying.
- Really?

11:16.143 --> 11:17.442
- I'll have the burger.
- Really.

11:17.444 --> 11:19.310
- Studying for what?
- For the s.A.T.S.

11:19.312 --> 11:21.046
- That test is in November.

11:21.048 --> 11:23.081
- Something to drink?
- Surprise me. Something stiff.

11:23.083 --> 11:25.050
- You know, your father and I
aren't morons.

11:25.052 --> 11:26.685
We know what it looks like

11:26.687 --> 11:28.153
When someone's been
[softly] smoking pot.

11:28.155 --> 11:30.021
- Oh, my god.
First of all, no you don't.

11:30.023 --> 11:32.023
Because I've been high, like,
50 times in the past year,

11:32.025 --> 11:33.958
And you have never noticed.
- Excuse me?

11:33.960 --> 11:35.894
- And second of all, is there
anything on this menu

11:35.896 --> 11:38.963
That's under 1,000 calories?
- Probably not, no.

11:38.965 --> 11:41.099
- That's what I thought.
I'll just have a diet coke.

11:41.101 --> 11:43.068
- Oh, for god's sake.
Now, hold it.

11:43.070 --> 11:46.037
Do you have a salad or--
- forget it. I'm not hungry.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.472
- Well, you have to eat.
- Can I have blueberry pancakes,

11:47.474 --> 11:49.441
Please?
- Excellent choice.

11:49.443 --> 11:51.209
- Look at it this way--if she's
not hungry, she's not high.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.944
- Oh, my god.

11:52.946 --> 11:56.047
- I could get the cooks
to make you an egg white omelet.

11:56.049 --> 11:58.416
- Fine.

11:59.452 --> 12:01.086
- Captain hook!

12:01.088 --> 12:03.221
- Oh, that's right.

12:03.223 --> 12:05.223
- Yeah, we have those at home.
Thank you.

12:05.225 --> 12:06.825
I'll have a lobster roll,
please.

12:06.827 --> 12:08.793
- Okay.
- Noah?

12:08.795 --> 12:11.262
- I--a lobster roll, too,
please.

12:11.264 --> 12:13.098
Thanks.
- You guys here on vacation?

12:13.100 --> 12:14.966
- Certainly are.
- For how long?

12:14.968 --> 12:16.401
- All summer, actually.

12:16.403 --> 12:19.070
- Well, welcome
to the end of the world.

12:22.208 --> 12:24.209
I'll go get these drinks.

12:29.348 --> 12:33.017
- Do you remember the first time
you saw her?

12:33.019 --> 12:35.153
- Like it was yesterday.

12:35.155 --> 12:37.355
- What do you remember?

12:37.357 --> 12:39.524
- I remember her face, asshole.

12:39.526 --> 12:41.092
What do you want me
to remember?

12:41.094 --> 12:42.393
- Noah?
- That's the one

12:42.395 --> 12:43.862
With the spikes.
- Noah. Noah!

12:43.864 --> 12:46.097
Is she choking?
- [gasps]

12:46.099 --> 12:47.866
- Stacey.
- Shit. What did she eat?

12:47.868 --> 12:49.300
[overlapping shouting]

12:49.302 --> 12:52.103
- All right, baby, come here.
- Oh, my god!

12:52.105 --> 12:54.105
- Try and spit it out.
Spit it out, stacey.

12:54.107 --> 12:55.440
Good girl.

12:55.442 --> 12:57.175
- Come on, honey.
Can you cough it up?

12:57.177 --> 12:58.376
Honey, look at me.
- Good girl, it's coming out.

12:58.378 --> 12:59.544
- Noah!
- It's all right, helen.

12:59.546 --> 13:01.179
All right.
- Spit it out.

13:01.181 --> 13:02.447
- Come on, good girl.
- Spit it out, stacey.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.249
- [coughs, gasps]
- good girl.

13:04.251 --> 13:05.984
- You're all right, honey.
- You're all right.

13:05.986 --> 13:07.852
You're all right.
- Oh, my god.

13:07.854 --> 13:09.921
- It's okay.
- Dad.

13:09.923 --> 13:11.856
- Come here, honey.
- Oh, my god, dad.

13:11.858 --> 13:13.258
- All right.
- Come here. Let me see.

13:13.260 --> 13:14.859
- Whitney, please.
- No, you totally

13:14.861 --> 13:16.427
Just saved her life.
- No, I didn't.

13:16.429 --> 13:18.997
- Yes, you did.
No, she was totally gonna die.

13:18.999 --> 13:20.932
- No, she wasn't.
- Yes, she was.

13:20.934 --> 13:22.567
- No, no, no, no, no.
- You don't always have to say

13:22.569 --> 13:24.135
Everything that pops
into your mouth.

13:24.137 --> 13:25.403
[stacey crying]
- I have to go to the bathroom.

13:25.405 --> 13:26.938
Let me out. I have to go now!
- Ow!

13:26.940 --> 13:28.339
- Come on.
- Trevor, get up.

13:28.341 --> 13:30.408
- But he hurt me.
- No, he didn't. Get up.

13:30.410 --> 13:32.310
Come on, it's all right.
- He pushed me off of there

13:32.312 --> 13:34.546
For no reason and he took--
- you're all right. Sit down.

13:34.548 --> 13:36.414
[stacey crying]
- what is happening here?

13:36.416 --> 13:37.849
- I have no idea.

13:38.951 --> 13:40.418
Martin, you in--

13:40.420 --> 13:41.586
Oh, I'm sorry.
- Oh.

13:41.588 --> 13:44.289
- I thought my son was--
- [sniffles]

13:44.291 --> 13:46.024
- You all right?

13:46.026 --> 13:48.293
What's the matter?
- Yeah, I am, I'm fine.

13:48.295 --> 13:50.428
Oh, [sighs] it's just your--

13:50.430 --> 13:52.163
Your daughter, uh--
- is that why you--

13:52.165 --> 13:54.098
- Yeah.
- Oh, please, she's a kid.

13:54.100 --> 13:57.368
You know, can't take your eyes
off of them.

13:57.370 --> 13:59.304
Hey, buddy.
- Hey.

13:59.306 --> 14:02.607
- What's goin' on?
- Nothing.

14:02.609 --> 14:05.243
- I was worried about you.
- Don't be.

14:06.946 --> 14:08.179
I'd better--

14:08.181 --> 14:10.915
- Yeah.
Your food will be up soon.

14:10.917 --> 14:12.617
- I'm noah, by the way.

14:12.619 --> 14:14.853
- [laughs]
I'm alison.

14:14.855 --> 14:17.388
- You sure you're okay?

14:17.390 --> 14:19.190
- [sniffs]
yeah. I'm fine.

14:22.595 --> 14:25.129
- How are you feeling, sweetie?
You okay?

14:25.131 --> 14:26.998
- Mm-hmm.
- Hmm?

14:27.000 --> 14:29.534
We'll be at grandma's soon,
and you can take a nap.

14:29.536 --> 14:31.402
- No nap.

14:36.976 --> 14:38.877
- Come here.

14:46.151 --> 14:48.620
She's okay.

14:48.622 --> 14:50.488
- No, I know.
[sniffles]

14:50.490 --> 14:53.091
I know.

14:53.093 --> 14:55.360
- Oh, shit.
- What?

14:55.362 --> 14:57.228
- I forgot to leave a tip.
- That's okay.

14:57.230 --> 14:59.097
- No, no.
They live on those tips.

14:59.099 --> 15:01.199
I'll be right back.

15:02.635 --> 15:05.637
[upbeat music]

15:05.639 --> 15:09.173
♪

15:09.175 --> 15:10.541
Miss.

15:10.543 --> 15:12.677
I forgot to leave a tip.
I'm so sorry.

15:12.679 --> 15:14.579
- Oh, no, no. That's okay.
- No, no, please.

15:14.581 --> 15:15.947
Please.
- No.

15:19.151 --> 15:21.920
Okay. Thanks.

15:24.123 --> 15:26.057
- Alison, right?

15:26.059 --> 15:28.593
- Yeah, that's right.

15:45.544 --> 15:48.479
- Well, here you are finally.

15:48.481 --> 15:51.316
Whitney, let me look at you.
- Hi, grandma.

15:51.318 --> 15:53.151
- Oh, my god.
You're so thin.

15:53.153 --> 15:55.153
Have you stopped eating
or something?

15:55.155 --> 15:56.554
- Practically, yes.

15:56.556 --> 15:58.456
- Well, keep it up.
You look fabulous.

15:58.458 --> 16:00.591
- It's not a behavior pattern
we want to encourage, mom.

16:00.593 --> 16:02.694
- Don't listen to your mother.
She was always a doughnut.

16:02.696 --> 16:04.696
Hi, honey.
- Hi, grandma.

16:04.698 --> 16:07.432
- Lose a couple more pounds,
and I'll take you to paris.

16:07.434 --> 16:09.467
- Hi, grandma.
- Hey, honey.

16:09.469 --> 16:13.304
- Oh, thanks, martin.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.006
- Ow.

16:17.076 --> 16:19.510
Dad, who's your least favorite
member of this family?

16:21.580 --> 16:23.715
- Uh, I don't really know how
to answer that question,

16:23.717 --> 16:25.450
Little man.

16:25.452 --> 16:27.185
- Let me put it to you
another way.

16:27.187 --> 16:29.721
If we were on a plane
and it was going to go down,

16:29.723 --> 16:32.523
And the pilot said you had
to push one family member out

16:32.525 --> 16:34.625
In order to save the rest of us,

16:34.627 --> 16:36.761
Who would it be?

16:36.763 --> 16:39.197
- That's easy.
I'd jump myself.

16:39.199 --> 16:40.465
- Oh.

16:40.467 --> 16:42.600
I was hoping you'd say martin.

16:42.602 --> 16:45.636
- [chuckles]

16:45.638 --> 16:48.272
We're family, little man.
We're stuck together.

16:50.142 --> 16:52.076
Come on.

16:54.480 --> 16:57.148
[sighs]

17:01.353 --> 17:04.355
[somber music]

17:04.357 --> 17:06.557
♪

17:06.559 --> 17:09.527
- I don't--
I was a happy man back then.

17:09.529 --> 17:12.764
I was proud of my family.
My first book had just come out.

17:12.766 --> 17:15.366
I'd--everything
I'd promised myself

17:15.368 --> 17:19.037
I'd achieve when I was
a young man, I...

17:19.039 --> 17:21.639
I'd done it.
- But?

17:21.641 --> 17:25.109
- Well, that's it.
There I no "but."

17:25.111 --> 17:27.245
When I look back, I...

17:27.247 --> 17:29.747
I can't tell you
what happened.

17:31.784 --> 17:33.551
- Noah.

17:33.553 --> 17:37.188
I thought I might be able
to interest you in an aperitif.

17:37.190 --> 17:39.190
- Oh, thanks, bruce.
I-I got a beer.

17:39.192 --> 17:41.059
- Where in the world
did you find that?

17:41.061 --> 17:43.327
- In the refrigerator.
- Huh.

17:43.329 --> 17:46.130
Must have been left
by one of the mexicans.

17:46.132 --> 17:49.667
A gift from paramount.

17:49.669 --> 17:51.269
- Oh, that's right.

17:51.271 --> 17:54.205
The new movie opens soon,
doesn't it?

