44:04.175 --> 44:12.181
♪

44:14.284 --> 44:16.419
[sniffles]

44:16.421 --> 44:20.056
[reading indistinctly]

44:32.269 --> 44:36.139
[indistinct conversation]

44:36.141 --> 44:41.744
[laughter]

44:41.746 --> 44:43.279
- [laughs]

44:43.281 --> 44:45.048
- And done!

44:45.050 --> 44:46.883
- He can pick it up tomorrow.
We can hang out tonight.

44:46.885 --> 44:48.418
- I'm free tonight.

44:48.420 --> 44:50.153
When he's doing something wrong,
he's mine.

44:50.155 --> 44:52.755
- All talk, that--that--
- how'd it go there?

44:52.757 --> 44:56.759
[overlapping chatter]

44:56.761 --> 44:58.161
[chatter stops]

45:05.202 --> 45:07.303
- There she is.

45:07.305 --> 45:10.306
Right on time.

45:10.308 --> 45:13.309
Oh.
- I'm sorry I'm late.

45:13.311 --> 45:14.811
- No, no, no, no.

45:14.813 --> 45:18.147
[indistinct conversation]

45:21.719 --> 45:23.252
- Mink oil.
- Mink oil?

45:23.254 --> 45:25.221
- He won't stop talking about
the mink oil.

45:25.223 --> 45:27.957
- It's not good--
it's not good quality, then.

45:27.959 --> 45:31.094
I said--I said
that a couple of--

45:31.096 --> 45:34.397
[overlapping chatter]

45:44.274 --> 45:46.275
- I learned it from a gypsy

45:46.277 --> 45:48.811
That came into the fish store
last month.

45:48.813 --> 45:51.948
I've been practicing.
It's really hard.

45:51.950 --> 45:54.383
Okay, let me see.

45:54.385 --> 45:57.220
Lucifer.
- Oh.

45:57.222 --> 45:59.222
- That's worrisome.
- Oh, no.

45:59.224 --> 46:01.357
Am I going to hell?

46:01.359 --> 46:04.894
- I'm not sure.
[laughs]

46:04.896 --> 46:07.296
Uh, let me look it up.

46:10.134 --> 46:13.402
It says here, "lucifer
is the card of temptation.

46:13.404 --> 46:17.840
"something is coming,
something powerful, wild.

46:17.842 --> 46:22.011
It may be a very good thing
or he may enslave you."

46:22.013 --> 46:24.280
- Hmm.

46:24.282 --> 46:25.548
- That's strange.

46:25.550 --> 46:27.550
What could that be?

46:27.552 --> 46:29.519
[both laugh]

46:29.521 --> 46:32.421
- Okay.

46:32.423 --> 46:34.123
- What about this one?

46:34.125 --> 46:36.826
- That's the page of cups.

46:41.999 --> 46:44.000
[distant laughter]

46:44.002 --> 46:46.469
- What is he?
Is he a child?

46:48.138 --> 46:50.439
- No, not necessarily.

46:50.441 --> 46:52.141
He's a messenger.

46:52.143 --> 46:55.878
Who, um...

46:55.880 --> 46:57.914
Let me see.

46:57.916 --> 47:00.583
He is like a child,
this messenger.

47:00.585 --> 47:03.219
He is very sensitive.

47:03.221 --> 47:06.122
You must be clear with him
or he may misunderstand you.

47:09.459 --> 47:11.327
- There you are.

47:11.329 --> 47:13.830
I've been lookin' everywhere
for you.

47:15.566 --> 47:18.901
I'm headed down to the bonfire.
You wanna come?

47:18.903 --> 47:22.605
- Can I meet you there
in a bit?

47:22.607 --> 47:24.607
- Sure, ali.

47:24.609 --> 47:27.276
You do whatever you want.

47:32.182 --> 47:34.050
- Are you guys okay?

47:34.052 --> 47:36.385
- Yeah, we're fine.

47:37.855 --> 47:40.056
God, you know,

47:40.058 --> 47:43.392
He never gives up, though.

47:43.394 --> 47:45.595
I gotta give him that.

47:45.597 --> 47:47.597
- Yeah.

47:47.599 --> 47:51.968
[distant chatter, laughter]

47:51.970 --> 47:54.403
- How old were you
when it began?

47:56.206 --> 47:59.275
- I was 31 years old.

47:59.277 --> 48:02.478
I remember promising myself
I'd get to 35.

48:02.480 --> 48:05.314
I'd make it through
till then.

48:06.617 --> 48:10.086
And if nothing had changed,

48:10.088 --> 48:12.088
Well, then,
I had tried hard enough.

48:14.625 --> 48:16.392
And cole,
cole was getting better.

48:16.394 --> 48:18.561
He was recovering.

48:18.563 --> 48:20.563
It was impossible for me.

48:20.565 --> 48:23.032
And I was so angry at him.

48:23.034 --> 48:26.168
I thought it seemed almost evil
to be happy.

48:34.544 --> 48:36.112
- Hello.

48:36.114 --> 48:37.647
- Oh, hi.

48:37.649 --> 48:39.582
- I found you.

48:39.584 --> 48:42.051
- Were you looking for me?

48:42.053 --> 48:43.653
- I'm kidding.
- Oh.

48:43.655 --> 48:47.523
- I was just on my way to check
out that bonfire over there.

48:47.525 --> 48:49.292
- Oh, wow.

48:49.294 --> 48:51.394
- You coming from there,
or you--

48:51.396 --> 48:55.131
- I, um--no, I, uh--

48:55.133 --> 48:58.567
- Well, too bad.
I could've used an introduction.

48:58.569 --> 49:00.569
- [laughs]
- you live around here?

49:00.571 --> 49:04.273
- Uh, yeah, a little farther up.
Ditch plains.

49:04.275 --> 49:05.541
What about you?

49:05.543 --> 49:08.010
- Just right over there,
actually

49:08.012 --> 49:10.146
- Really?

49:10.148 --> 49:12.415
- Oh, it's not my house.
It belongs to my father-in-law.

49:12.417 --> 49:15.418
- Your father-in-law's
bruce butler?

49:15.420 --> 49:17.320
- Yeah. You know him?

49:17.322 --> 49:19.422
- Yeah. Well, who doesn't?
- Oh, right.

49:19.424 --> 49:22.258
Yeah, yeah, I guess
he's--he's pretty famous.

49:24.428 --> 49:26.195
- Well, you know,
I-I don't want to keep you.

49:26.197 --> 49:28.164
- No, no, no, please.
No, please, it's okay.

49:28.166 --> 49:30.566
I would probably feel
kind of weird going over there.

49:30.568 --> 49:32.568
Those people look way too cool.
- [laughs]

49:32.570 --> 49:34.503
No, they're not, really.

49:34.505 --> 49:38.441
- Well, maybe not for you,
but I get easily intimidated.

49:38.443 --> 49:41.444
- [laughs]
- you wanna smoke?

49:41.446 --> 49:44.613
- No, I-I don't smoke.
- Neither do I.

49:44.615 --> 49:46.649
- You were offering me
a cigarette.

49:46.651 --> 49:48.517
- Yeah, I know.
I should amend that.

49:48.519 --> 49:50.519
I don't smoke
except when I'm on vacation.

49:50.521 --> 49:53.189
And even then, I only let myself
smoke french cigarettes.

49:53.191 --> 49:55.091
- Why?

49:55.093 --> 49:56.726
- It's a self-regulatory
mechanism

49:56.728 --> 49:59.195
I've developed
over many years.

49:59.197 --> 50:01.063
'cause they're so impossible
to come by,

50:01.065 --> 50:03.499
I usually give up
before I find one.

50:03.501 --> 50:06.268
- [laughs]

50:06.270 --> 50:08.137
- Come on.

50:08.139 --> 50:10.272
They're gauloises.

50:13.110 --> 50:15.277
- [chuckles]
okay.

50:20.384 --> 50:22.752
- I'm noah, in case you were--
- I remember.

50:22.754 --> 50:26.088
I'm alison.

50:26.090 --> 50:28.357
- I'm really sorry
about today.

50:28.359 --> 50:30.359
I've been wondering how I could
possibly ever repay you.

50:30.361 --> 50:32.128
- No, you don't have to
do anything. I--

50:32.130 --> 50:33.763
- No, you don't understand
the way my brain works.

50:33.765 --> 50:36.232
I'm totally neurotic.
This is gonna haunt me for years

50:36.234 --> 50:38.501
Unless I buy you a pony
or something.

50:38.503 --> 50:40.703
- I don't want a pony.

50:40.705 --> 50:42.171
- You see,
now you're making it worse.

50:42.173 --> 50:43.606
- [laughs]

50:46.176 --> 50:48.444
- Listen, could I...

50:48.446 --> 50:50.179
Walk you home?
I mean,

50:50.181 --> 50:52.481
Would you let me do that?

50:56.386 --> 50:58.354
- Okay.

51:04.728 --> 51:06.796
- This is where you live?

51:06.798 --> 51:08.697
- Mm, yeah.

51:08.699 --> 51:10.533
- Wow, this place is great.

51:10.535 --> 51:12.401
- Thanks.

51:12.403 --> 51:14.537
- Is that an outdoor shower?

51:14.539 --> 51:17.073
- Uh, yeah.
- Oh, man.

51:17.075 --> 51:19.809
I've always wanted one of those.
Can I check it out?

51:19.811 --> 51:21.777
- Sure. Yeah.

51:29.086 --> 51:30.820
- Wow.

51:32.155 --> 51:34.090
[laughs] wow.
- [giggles]

51:34.092 --> 51:37.760
- This is my idea
of happiness.

51:37.762 --> 51:41.397
- Uh, do you want
to try it?

51:47.170 --> 51:50.439
- No, I should--

51:50.441 --> 51:52.708
I should go home.

51:54.611 --> 51:56.879
- Okay.

51:56.881 --> 51:59.648
Well, thanks for the walk.

52:07.891 --> 52:11.260
Oh. No.

52:11.262 --> 52:13.262
- I--sorry, that was--

52:13.264 --> 52:15.464
I don't know--
I don't know why I did that.

52:17.534 --> 52:19.401
I'd say it was 'cause
I'm french,

52:19.403 --> 52:21.604
But I'd clearly be lying.

52:24.207 --> 52:26.876
- Well...

52:26.878 --> 52:28.744
- I guess I'll see you
around town?

52:28.746 --> 52:32.615
- Yeah, there's no real way
to avoid it.

52:39.489 --> 52:42.491
[dramatic music]

52:42.493 --> 52:50.499
♪

53:08.919 --> 53:11.921
[rock music playing over radio]

53:11.923 --> 53:13.589
♪

53:13.591 --> 53:15.691
- No way.

53:15.693 --> 53:18.260
♪

53:18.262 --> 53:19.328
[music stops]
- all right.

53:19.330 --> 53:20.563
Thanks for the ride.

53:20.565 --> 53:22.932
- You're welcome.
It was fun.

53:22.934 --> 53:24.533
- Yeah, it was fun.

53:24.535 --> 53:26.635
